Vice President Harris provided a six-month progress report on the Biden-Harris Action Plan for Building Better School Infrastructure, highlighting actions taken to improve public schools' facilities and transportation. In Seattle, Washington, she announced nearly $1 billion in rebate awards from President Biden's Bipartisan Infrastructure Law to replace old school buses with clean ones. The plan aims to deliver safer, healthier, and more sustainable learning environments, save money for school districts, create jobs, and address climate change. Other actions announced include upgrading school infrastructure, supporting clean energy in rural schools, and improving indoor air quality. The Biden-Harris Administration is committed to ensuring that students have safe and healthy school environments to learn and thrive.